      "type": "markdown",
      "text": "For example, define the function f such that f(x) = x(x). Any function passed as an argument to f is invoked with itself as an argument, and thus in any use of that argument is indirectly referring to itself."
    },
    {
      "id": "b4635525-c2ae-411e-b349-047476e3c0c2",
